name: MTLCommandBufferError
desc: Error codes that indicate why the execution of the command buffer has failed.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string containing the localized description of the error.

items.name: static var timeout: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: Execution of the command buffer took more time than the system allows, so execution was interrupted and aborted.

items.name: static var pageFault: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: Execution of the command buffer generated an unserviceable GPU page fault.

items.name: static var blacklisted: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: Access to the Metal device has been revoked because this client has been responsible for too many timeouts or hangs.

items.name: static var notPermitted: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: The process does not have permission to use the Metal device.

items.name: static var outOfMemory: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: Insufficient memory was available to execute the command buffer.

items.name: static var invalidResource: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: The command buffer referenced an invalid resource.

items.name: static var memoryless: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: One or more internal resource limits were reached that prevent using memoryless render pass attachments.

items.name: static var deviceRemoved: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: The GPU that executes the commands has been removed.

items.name: static var `internal`: MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: An internal error that doesn't fit into the other categories.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: The error domain used by a command buffer when returning command buffer execution errors.

items.name: static func != (MTLCommandBufferError, MTLCommandBufferError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.

items.name: enum MTLCommandBufferError.Code
items.desc: Error codes that indicate why the execution of the command buffer has failed. The error property contains the error code.
